Limited Exception for Commentary, Review, and Gameplay

Notwithstanding the "Restrictions" section above, limited permission is granted to reproduce, distribute, or transmit a Work (e.g., a musical composition or visual asset) from this repository only when it is captured as an incidental part of, or is the direct subject of, content such as:

Gameplay videos, tutorials, or live streams of a project (e.g., a video game) that the Work is an official part of.

Bona fide commentary, analysis, review, or documentary footage where the Work itself, or the project it is part of, is the primary subject.

Example of Permitted Use: A "Let's Play" video, live stream, or video review that showcases gameplay of the video game that the song or asset is an official part of.

Example of Permitted Use: A video documentary that discusses the video game and utilizes the song while analyzing the game's soundtrack.

Example of Prohibited Use: Using a song from this repository as background music for a video, stream, or podcast on a topic unrelated to the song or the project it is part of.

Example of Prohibited Use: Using a song from this repository as background music for a gameplay video of a different game that the song is not part of.

This limited exception does not grant any rights to:

Create derivative works, including but not limited to remixes, covers, arrangements, or modifications.

Use the Work as general background music for content that is not directly about the Work or the specific project the Work is an official part of.

Isolate the Work (e.g., the audio track) from its original project and re-upload it or distribute it standalone.

Any use outside of this specific exception remains subject to the "Restrictions" section and requires the prior written permission of the author(s).

